ex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xnc1665702891206.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnc1665702891206.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xnc1665702891206.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xnc1665702891206\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Calling Windows GetLastError() Function\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__calling_windows_getlasterrorfunction_110718\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ULASTERROR</span> rather than calling <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetLastError()</code>.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__p_d34637e1_d34638e1_d34639e1\">If you use Uniface to activate Windows API functions, and you want to do error handling, you find that activating <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetLastError()</code> always returns zero instead of the error from the last activated Windows call.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__p_d34640e1_d34641e1_d34642e1\">To get the actual error information, in a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ULASTERROR</span>, which returns the saved return value of <code class=\"ph codeph\">GetLastError()</code> from the previous <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> in that same signature.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__p_d34643e1_d34644e1_d34645e1\">Alternatively, you can give the operation a different name, such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">GETLASTERROR</code>, and give it the literal name <code class=\"ph codeph\">ULASTERROR</code> (all in uppercase).</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__note_w5716ab1b5b9_w5717ab1b5_w5718ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> This is implemented for Windows only. On other platforms, the string\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">ULASTERROR</code> in a signature has no special meaning.</div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__note_w5719ab1b5c11_w5720ab1b5_w5721ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Each signature instance has its own copy of the saved error value, and\n         therefore each signature must have its own <code class=\"ph codeph\">ULASTERROR</code> pseudo-operation\n         defined.</div>\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__p_d34646e1_d34647e1_d34648e1\">For example, given the following code, the second activate call returns <code class=\"ph codeph\">123 ('Invalid name')</code> as expected.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">activate \"SIG1\".SETCURRENTDIRECTORY(\"@#$%^&amp;*\")\nactivate \"SIG1\".ULASTERROR() </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xnc1665702891206__p_d34649e1_d34650e1_d34651e1\">However, the following command returns <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">activate \"SIG2\".ULASTERROR()</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533806\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Calling Windows GetLastError() Function Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Calling Windows GetLastError() Function In a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name ULASTERROR rather than calling GetLastError() . If you use Uniface to activate Windows API functions, and you want to do error handling, you find that activating GetLastError() always returns zero instead of the error from the last activated Windows call. To get the actual error information, in a 3GL signature used to call Windows API functions, you can define a pseudo-operation with the name ULASTERROR , which returns the saved return value of GetLastError() from the previous activate in that same signature. Alternatively, you can give the operation a different name, such as GETLASTERROR , and give it the literal name ULASTERROR (all in uppercase). Note: This is implemented for Windows only. On other platforms, the string ULASTERROR in a signature has no special meaning. Note: Each signature instance has its own copy of the saved error value, and therefore each signature must have its own ULASTERROR pseudo-operation defined. For example, given the following code, the second activate call returns 123 ('Invalid name') as expected. activate \"SIG1\".SETCURRENTDIRECTORY(\"@#$%^&*\") activate \"SIG1\".ULASTERROR() Copy However, the following command returns 0 . activate \"SIG2\".ULASTERROR() Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}